   "source": [
    "# Morphology Classification\n",
    "Let's put the entire pipeline together: generating point clouds, computing structural observables (features), and training an ML classifier to separate Elliptical (0), Spiral (1), and Irregular (2) galaxies."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import shap\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from galaxyclouds.io import generate_synthetic_galaxies\n",
    "from galaxyclouds.classification import build_feature_matrix, train_morphology_classifier, evaluate_classifier, compare_frame_performance\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.style.use('dark_background')\n",
    "X, y = generate_synthetic_galaxies(n_per_class=1000, seed=42)\n",
    "mask = X[:, :, 0] > 0\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compare Frames\n",
    "compare_frame_performance(X, y, mask)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_feats = build_feature_matrix(X, mask, use_galaxy_frame=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df_feats, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "model = train_morphology_classifier(X_train, y_train, model_type='xgboost')\n",
    "results = evaluate_classifier(model, X_test, y_test)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# SHAP Feature Importance\n",
    "explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(model)\n",
    "shap_values = explainer.shap_values(X_test)\n",
    "shap.summary_plot(shap_values, X_test, plot_type=\"bar\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Interpreting SHAP\n",
    "The most discriminating feature is stellar multiplicity because it cleanly correlates with the degree of ongoing star formation. Elliptical galaxies uniformly present as concentrated low-multiplicity point clouds in simulated SDSS conditions.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What would improve this?\n",
    "- Add spectral features.\n",
    "- Use graph neural networks directly on the point cloud rather than engineered structural moments.\n",
    "- Implement self-supervised learning pre-training akin to masked particle modeling in jet physics."
   ]
  }
